title: Jimmie Allen In-Studio on How He Got Famous and His Early Encounters with Country Stars + Chris Stapleton on What Kind of A Student He Was in High School +  Eddie Wants to Know How Much Does Baby Bitter Cost?
itunes:title: Jimmie Allen In-Studio on How He Got Famous and His Early Encounters with Country Stars + Chris Stapleton on What Kind of A Student He Was in High School +  Eddie Wants to Know How Much Does Baby Bitter Cost?
description:
Jimmie Allen stops by the studio to talk about how he got famous, deciding to move to Nashville out of nowhere and running into country artists as he was just getting his start in music. We talk to Chris Stapleton about his single “You Should Probably Leave” and how he actually wrote it a long time ago. He also tells us about what his hometown was like and how he first got started playing music. Eddie brings in the question of how much do you pay a babysitter?
